Cursor Update Rule

Whenever Cursor adds, removes, or modifies any file in a folder, it must:

Check for a README.md.

If found, append a timestamped ## 📆 Update Log section (if not present) and describe the change.

If not found, create a new README.md with the standard structure.

Copy the file to /docs/modules/<folder>.md.

🛠️ Notes

Readme changes should never overwrite existing context without preserving history.


When uncertain, Cursor must annotate its update with // TODO: Verify and describe assumptions.